                    <p style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:11px"><span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif">(hereinafter collectively/individually referred to as the <strong>Second Party/the Beneficiary</strong>).</span></span></p>

                    <p style="margin-left:-1px; margin-right:8px; text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:11px"><span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif"><strong>PREAMBLE</strong></span></span></p>

                    <p style="margin-left:23px; margin-right:8px; text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:11px"><span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif">The First Party is the Legal Representative and Manager of The Myriad Muscat property located in Al Khoud (the <strong>&lsquo;Property&rsquo;</strong>). The Property consists of furnished rooms licensed to be rented with beds according to the room type and the period agreed upon with the Second Party. The Second Party has checked the room and bed along with other amenities therein, examined the terms and conditions related to their stay in the Myriad Muscat and accepted the same. The Parties have agreed on the following terms and conditions:</span></span></p>

                    <p style="margin-right:8px"><span style="font-size:11px"><span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif"><strong>Article (1):</strong></span></span></p>

                    <p style="margin-left:23px; margin-right:8px; text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:11px"><span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif">The above Preamble constitutes an integral put hereof, to be read with and complement the Agreement.</span></span></p>

                    <p style="margin-right:8px"><span style="font-size:11px"><span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif"><strong>Article (2):</strong></span></span></p>

                    <p style="margin-left:23px; margin-right:8px; text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:11px"><span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif">The Second Party shall acknowledge and agree to all terms and conditions included in the Annexes attached hereto. If any amendment was made to the Annexes, the Second Party would be informed, and the Annexes shall be in effect as of their date and be binding on both parties.</span></span></p>

                    <p><span style="font-size:11px"><span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif"><strong>Article (3):</strong></span></span></p>

                    <p style="margin-left:23px; text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:11px"><span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif">Not to sub-let or assign the whole, or any part, of the room or Property or share occupation of the room. Normal and reasonable residential use of electricity, gas, water, and sewerage utility services is included within the rent. The First Party reserves the right to charge the Second Party for non-residential or unreasonable or excessive use of such services.&nbsp; </span></span></p>

                    <p style="margin-left:23px; text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:11px"><span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif">In the event of an increase in the prices related to the utilities or services provided under this agreement, the first party shall bear the responsibility of paying the difference resulting from this increase. This includes all additional costs that may arise due to the increase in market prices.</span></span></p>

                    <p style="margin-right:8px"><span style="font-size:11px"><span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif"><strong>Article (4):</strong></span></span></p>

                    <p style="margin-left:23px; text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:11px"><span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif">Not to damage the property/room or its Content or to make alterations or additions unless with the prior express <strong>written consent</strong> of the Landlord. To ensure the interior of the Property in always maintained in good and clean&nbsp;&nbsp; condition. Further to this no personal goods to be kept in common areas.</span></span></p>

                    <p style="margin-right:8px"><span style="font-size:11px"><span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif"><strong>Article (5):</strong></span></span></p>

                    <p style="margin-left:23px; text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:11px"><span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif">The Second Party shall pay the First Party the agreed rent in advance as per the payment schedule set for this purpose without making any deduction or set-off therefrom. If the Second Party fails to make a payment of the rent on the due date (7 days after the payment due date), the First Party will be entitled at its sole discretion to remarket the room for re-letting and/or deny access to the room from the date the payment was due. </span></span></p>

                    <p style="margin-right:8px"><span style="font-size:11px"><span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif"><strong>Article (6):</strong></span></span></p>

                    <p style="margin-left:23px; margin-right:8px; text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:11px"><span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif">The Second Party shall pay a security deposit upon reservation, to be held with the First Party until the elapse of the lease. The First Party is entitled to deduct its amount, in whole or in part, against unpaid amounts of rent and any other amounts incurred from damage to the room, its accessories, contents, common areas, equipment, furniture, losses and any fines arising from violations created due to the Second Party&#39;s actions.</span></span></p>

                    <p style="margin-left:23px; margin-right:8px; text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:11px"><span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif">The First Party reserves the right to retain the security deposit if the room is not returned in the same condition it was received.</span></span></p>

                    <p style="margin-left:-1px; margin-right:8px"><span style="font-size:11px"><span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif"><strong>Article (7):</strong></span></span></p>

                    <p style="margin-left:23px; margin-right:8px; text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:11px"><span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif">The First Party male and/or female workers shall have the right to enter rooms at all reasonable times during the term of this lease for the purposes of inspection, maintenance, repair, alteration and show the accommodation to prospective new tenants. </span></span></p>

                    <p style="margin-left:-1px; margin-right:8px"><span style="font-size:11px"><span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif"><strong>Article (8):</strong></span></span></p>

                    <p style="margin-left:23px; margin-right:8px; text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:11px"><span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif">In the case of joint rooms, the liability shall be jointly and severally shared among the occupants towards the damages resulting from the breach of the terms and conditions contained in the Articles of this Agreement.</span></span></p>

